{
  "text": "Weibull factors k and c demonstrate the distribution of the winds for a particular location [CITATION_1] . The following scale is implemented to measure the degree of wind availability: good-f (V) \u2265 0.90; average-0.75 \u2264 f (V) < 0.90; and low-f (V) < 0.75.",
